Metadata-Version: 1.0
Name: vortex.recipe.setup-install
Version: 1.0dev
Summary: zc.buildout recipe for creating files from file templates
Home-page: http://vortexdna.com/
Author: Darryl Cousins
Author-email: darryl.cousins@treefernwebservices.co.nz
License: UNKNOWN
Description: The ``vortex.recipe.setup_install`` recipe installs a python package using
        'setup.py install'.
        
        We have an archive with a demo foo tar ball:
        
        >>> ls(distros)
        -  foo.tgz
        
        Now let's create a buildout configuration so that we can test the buildout.
        
        >>> write(sample_buildout, 'buildout.cfg',
        ... """
        ... [buildout]
        ... index = http://download.zope.org/zope3.4
        ... parts = foo
        ...
        ... [foo]
        ... recipe = vortex.recipe.setup_install
        ... url = file://%s/foo.tgz
        ... """ % distros)
        
        Run the buildout
        
        >>> print system(buildout)
        Getting distribution for 'zc.recipe.cmmi'.
        Got zc.recipe.cmmi 1.1.0.
        Installing foo.
        foo: Downloading
        file:///tmp/tmp...buildoutSetUp/_TEST_/distros/foo.tgz
        foo: Unpacking and configuring
        configuring foo install
        
        
        If the package is found (by ``import package``) then it is not installed.
        
        >>> write(sample_buildout, 'buildout.cfg',
        ... """
        ... [buildout]
        ... index = http://download.zope.org/zope3.4
        ... parts = foo
        ...
        ... [foo]
        ... recipe = vortex.recipe.setup_install
        ... url = file://%s/foo.tgz
        ... package = os
        ... """ % distros)
        
        Run the buildout
        
        >>> print system(buildout)
        Uninstalling foo.
        Installing foo.
        foo: Package os found for ...
        
        
        Changes
        =======
        
        0.1dev
        ------
        
        Initial import.
        
